Content: BarterDEX's coin list system has been changed to allow for so many coins being added (in excess of 256). The change was to reduce the amount of coins on startup, use a call to update the coins list dynamically (rather than waiting for an updated release or having "releases" for the sake of coins list), and have users add whatever they want. @12thandgrantco

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content:
to trade eth/erc20 in barterdex,
- go to manage coins
- add coins from left pane to the list
- add as many fav coins you want
- restart barterdex. close, open again, login.
- enable coins with add coin button
- must enable ETOMIC, before enabling any other ETH or ERC20 coin.

get help further from community in #dev-tradebots
